About Boot
Multiple Boot Pen Drive

1. Copy and install the necessary Pmagci, bt4 files on the usb stick

2. Edit the /boot/grub/grub.cfg, here's mine

menuentry "pmagic rescure toolkit on usb-p1" {

set root='(hd0,1)'

linux /pmagic/bzImage

initrd /pmagic/initramfs

}

menuentry "bt 4 on usb-p5" {

set root='(hd0,5)'

linux /boot/vmlinuz boot=casper

initrd /boot/initrd.gz

}

menuentry "t410 ubuntu on p5" {

set root='(hd1,5)'

linux /vmlinuz

intird /initrd.gz

}

menuentry "usb the live cd to install ubuntu" {

loopback loop /boot/iso/ubuntu-11.04-desktop-i386.iso

linux (loop)/casper/vmlinuz boot=casper iso-scan/filename=/ubuntu-11.04-desktop-i386.iso noeject noprompt --

initrd (loop)/casper/initrd.lz

}

tip: you have put your ubuntu live cd to a FAT32 partition.

Installation from a USB or Pen Drive

Sharp Tools
Multi-Media
Burn CD/DVD

http://www.cyberciti.biz/tips/howto-linux-write-burn-data-to-dvd-or-dvdrw.html
$ sudo apt-get install dvd+rw-tools

Make ISO
$ sudo mkisofs -r -o /tmp/var-www-disk1.iso /var/www

Burn ISO
$ sudo growisofs -Z /dev/dvd=/tmp/var-www-disk1.iso

Append
$ sudo growisofs -M /dev/dvd /tmp/file.1

Format
$ sudo dvd+rw-format -force /dev/dvd
